HEADWORD: Providential
<hw>Prov`i*den"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>providentiel</ets>.]</ety> <def>Effected by, or referable to,
divine direction or superintendence; <as>as, the <ex>providential</ex>
contrivance of thing; a <ex>providential</ex> escape.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>Prov"i*den"tial*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

